
Send packets to a HiDes modulator device

Usage: tsp -O hides [options]

Options:

  -a value
  --adapter value
      Specify the HiDes adapter number to use. By default, the first HiDes
      device is selected. Use the command tshides to list all HiDes devices.

  -b value
  --bandwidth value
      Bandwidth in Hz. For compatibility with old versions, low values (below
      1000) are interpreted in MHz. The default is 8,000,000 for DVB-T/T2.

  -c value
  --constellation value
      Constellation type. The default is 64-QAM.
      The 'value' must be one of "16-QAM", "64-QAM", "QPSK".

  --dc-compensation i-value/q-value
      Specify the DC offset compensation values for I and Q. Each offset value
      shall be in the range -512 to 512.

  -d name
  --device name
      Specify the HiDes device name to use. By default, the first HiDes device
      is selected. Use the command tshides to list all HiDes devices.

  -f value
  --frequency value
      Frequency, in Hz, of the output carrier. This parameter is mandatory.
      There is no default.

  --gain value
      Adjust the output gain to the specified value in dB. The allowed gain
      range depends on the device, the frequency and the bandwidth.

  -g value
  --guard-interval value
      Guard interval. The default is 1/32.
      The 'value' must be one of "1/4", "1/8", "1/16", "1/32".

  --help
      Display this help text.

  -h value
  --high-priority-fec value
      Error correction for high priority streams. The default is 2/3.
      The 'value' must be one of "1/2", "2/3", "3/4", "5/6", "7/8".

  -s value
  --spectral-inversion value
      Spectral inversion. The default is auto.
      The 'value' must be one of "auto", "off", "on".

  -t value
  --transmission-mode value
      Transmission mode. The default is 8K.
      The 'value' must be one of "2K", "4K", "8K".

